ğŸ”§ A Directive is a special instruction in Angular that adds behavior to elements in the DOM (HTML).

There are three types of directives in Angular:
1ï¸âƒ£ Component Directive:
âœ… Every component is actually a directive with a template.
Created using @Component decorator.
